column5: Started packing the boat away today and I just can't do it!  There has to be at least one last trip to be had...  Was out on LSC for a spectacular day on Monday but the temp and wind forecast has me thinking that was the last big water day of the year..  I haven't fished for walleye since May so it would be nice to go out and try to find enough for a dinner.  Obvious choice is the Kawarthas.. being from Kitchener I don't want to drive much over 2 hours.  BOQ is just too far for a day trip..  Thoughts?
Come to the KA area in the next few days and I'll hope in the boat with you and show you a lake just outside of the Lindsay area...
Come to the KA area in the next few days and I'll hope in the boat with you and show you a lake just outside of the Lindsay area...  PM sent :-)
Lakers open back up Dec 1st in Lake Ontario.  Then hit the Niagara bar.
PS, I don't look like the avatar... I have less hair up top... lol
